    <section id="id-234">
      <title>Impulse response for causal system and signal</title>
      <para id="id4396327">Since impulse response is a characterization (among other characterizations) of systems. As such, the causality of a system would be reflected on its impulse response. From the convolution  <link target-id="id0028b" strength="2"> Figure </link>  the output at instant 
<m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mstyle fontsize="12pt"><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mstyle fontsize="8pt"><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{n rSub { size 8{0} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> is:</para>
      <para id="id4396393"><m:math display="block">
          <m:semantics>
